				<li id="16756765" class="cmnt-root" data="5" data-d="1660545781000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579182/Mohgwyn's-Sacred-Spear" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">15 Aug 2022 02:43</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16756765" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">You can powerstance them, it satisfies my elden bling and it&apos;s quite effective. You can first use the WA of the left one 2 handed, then switch back to powerstance and use the WA of the right one, so you can light both of them. Also as someone said you can get some health back by putting the blasphemous blade on your back, you don&apos;t even need to meet the requirements for the weapon (not sure if it&apos;s intended, but still working for 1.6). The moveset is awesome, 2 handed or with powerstance (which is quite rare). It&apos;s a bit weird that I don&apos;t see more people powerstancing them, but I guess you can get a higher damage in 1 hit with other greatspears. I don&apos;t regret my shameful transition from my Bonk Bonk build, I&apos;m doing more damage with jump attacks than with 2 colossal weapons (I&apos;m not joking...). And almost every move in the moveset are not only usable but very effective for both Pve and Pvp. And you can trigger bleed very fast if something is using a shield for example. And split fire damage means longer staggering animations for everything weak to fire (there are a lot of enemies, see the fire damage page) + higher damage for critical hits (eg I&apos;m doing just a bit less critical damage than with my cold misricorde). And the gold cherry on top of the cake is of course the weapon art, but I&apos;ll stop here otherwise fromsoft will nerf this weapon into the ground and we&apos;ll be left with boring dual cross-naginata buids...</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16756765" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16756765" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>5</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16756765"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16756765" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16756765"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
